<inglise> of 12 October 1999 imposing further testing requirements on the importers or manufacturers of a certain priority substance as foreseen under Council Regulation (EEC) No 793/93 on the evaluation and control of the risks of existing substances </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2161/1999, millega kehtestatakse t&auml;iendavad kontrollin&otilde;uded &uuml;he teatava erit&auml;helepanu n&otilde;udva kemikaali importijatele ja tootjatele vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 registreeritud kemikaalide ohtlikkuse hindamise ja kontrolli kohta 12. oktoober 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 793/93 of 23 March 1993 on the evaluation and control of the risks of existing substances(1) and in particular Article 10(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. m&auml;rtsi 1993. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 registreeritud kemikaalide ohtlikkuse hindamise ja kontrolli kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 10 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas Article 10 of Regulation (EEC) No 793/93 foresees that the Member State "Rapporteur" for a given substance shall be responsible for evaluating the information submitted by the manufacturer(s) or importer(s) and for identifying, after consultation of the producers or importers concerned whether for the purposes of the risk evaluation it is necessary to require the above manufacturers or importers to submit further information or to carry out further testing; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 artikkel 10 n&auml;eb ette, et teatava aine referendiks olev liikmesriik vastutab tootja(te) v&otilde;i importija(te) esitatud informatsiooni hindamise eest ning, p&auml;rast konsulteerimist asjaomaste tootjate v&otilde;i importijatega, selle kindlakstegemise eest, kas kemikaali ohtlikkuse hindamiseks on vaja n&otilde;uda eespool nimetatud tootjatelt v&otilde;i importijatelt lisateabe esitamist v&otilde;i t&auml;iendavaid katseid; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the Commission has been informed by one Member State Rapporteur of the need to impose on the importers or manufacturers of a certain priority substance undergoing risk evaluation activities a request for further testing within certain time limits; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) &uuml;ks referentliikmesriik on komisjonile teatanud vajadusest n&otilde;uda seoses &uuml;he konkreetse erit&auml;helepanu n&otilde;udva kemikaaliga, mille ohtlikkuse hindamine on k&auml;imas, et selle importijad v&otilde;i tootjad teeksid teatava t&auml;htaja jooksul t&auml;iendavaid katseid; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas Article 12 of Regulation (EEC) No 793/93 foresees that in the case of a substance produced or imported as such or in a preparation by several manufacturers/importers, the further testing may be performed by one manufacturer/importer acting on behalf of the other manufacturers/importers concerned who shall make reference to the tests carried out and shall make a fair and equitable contribution to the cost; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 artikkel 12 n&auml;eb ette, et juhul kui kemikaali toodab v&otilde;i impordib eraldi v&otilde;i preparaadi koostises mitu tootjat v&otilde;i importijat, v&otilde;ib t&auml;iendavad katsed teha &uuml;ks tootja v&otilde;i importija, kes tegutseb teiste asjaomaste tootjate v&otilde;i importijate nimel; teised asjaomased tootjad v&otilde;i importijad peavad viitama niiviisi tehtud katsetele ja tasuma &otilde;iglase osa nende maksumusest; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the provisions of this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee established pursuant to Article 15 of Regulation (EEC) No 793/93, </inglise>
<eesti> 4) k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tted on koosk&otilde;las m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 artikli 15 alusel loodud komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The manufacturer(s) and importer(s), referred to in Article 10(1) of Regulation (EEC) No 793/93, of the substance listed in the Annex to the present Regulation, shall perform the test there indicated and shall deliver the relevant results to the Member State Rapporteur. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 793/93 artikli 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud tootja(d) ja importija(d) viib (viivad) l&auml;bi katsed k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas nimetatud ainega ja edastab (edastavad) vastavad tulemused referentliikmesriigile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> These results shall be delivered within the time limits also indicated in the Annex (calculated from the date of entry into force of this Regulation). </inglise>
<eesti> Tulemused esitatakse t&auml;htaja jooksul, mis on samuti esitatud lisas (ja mida arvestatakse alates k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumisest) </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 12 October 1999. </inglise>
